Introduction, Lettering, 2d Geometrical Constructions

1- Write (Manually or using CAD software) the Capital letters A to Z, small letters a to z, and Arabic numbers 0 to 9 with 0.7 mm thick - lines and 0.5 mm thick line pencils.

2- Draw Margins and Title block in drawing sheet. 

3- Draw the basic 2D geometric entities, each of dimension or side or radius of 30mm (a vertical straight line, a horizontal straight line, an equilateral triangle, a square, a regular pentagon, a regular hexagon, and a circle. With labels and dimensions. (Students should learn drawing other regular polygonal shapes also)
